# Phase 3: Model Building and Evaluation

## Objective

The objective of this phase is to build a machine learning model using the preprocessed dataset and evaluate its performance in predicting student outcomes.

---

## Data Preparation

The processed dataset was divided into:

* Features (X): All input variables
* Target (y): Final_Grade

The data was then split into training and testing sets to evaluate performance on unseen data.

---

## Train-Test Split

The dataset was split as follows:

* 80% for training
* 20% for testing

This ensures that the model is trained on one portion of data and tested on another.

---

## Model Used

### Random Forest Regressor

Since the target variable Final_Grade is numerical, a regression model was used.

Random Forest Regressor was chosen because:

* It handles non-linear relationships effectively
* It reduces overfitting
* It provides reliable performance without heavy tuning

---

## Model Training

The model was trained using the training dataset to learn patterns between input features and the target variable.

---

## Prediction

After training, predictions were made on the test dataset to evaluate how well the model performs on unseen data.

---

## Model Evaluation

The model was evaluated using:

* Mean Absolute Error (MAE)
* Mean Squared Error (MSE)
* R² Score

These metrics help measure how close the predicted values are to the actual values.

---

## Results

The model achieved satisfactory performance in predicting student grades. The predictions were reasonably close to the actual values, indicating that the model learned meaningful patterns from the data.

---

## Conclusion of Phase 3

The machine learning model was successfully trained and evaluated. The results show that student performance can be effectively predicted using features such as study hours, attendance, and previous academic performance.

